## 1. Acceptance of Terms
By installing and using the Gmail Spam Filter Chrome extension (the "Extension"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the Extension.

## 2. Description of Service
The Extension is designed to help users identify and flag potential spam messages in their Gmail inbox using AI-based classification. It requires permission to access your Gmail inbox using OAuth 2.0.

## 3. User Responsibilities
You agree to use the Extension only for lawful purposes and in accordance with Gmail's own Terms of Service. Misuse of the Extension, including unauthorized data scraping, is strictly prohibited.

## 4. Data Access and Usage
The Extension uses the following Google OAuth scope:

- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly`

This access is used only to read email content and classify spam. No data is stored, retained, or shared outside of your browser session.

